---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
import FinancialModel from "../components/FinancialModel";
---

<MainLayout title="JustCook - Financial Model & Projections">
	<main class="financials-page">
		<section class="intro-section">
			<div class="container">
				<nav class="breadcrumb">
					<a href="/">&larr; Back to Home</a>
				</nav>
				<h1>Financial Model & Projections</h1>
				<p class="intro-text">
					Explore JustCook's unit economics and financial projections through interactive models. 
					Adjust key assumptions to see how different scenarios impact our path to profitability.
				</p>
				
				<div class="key-assumptions">
					<h2>Key Business Assumptions</h2>
					<div class="assumptions-grid">
						<div class="assumption-card">
							<h3>Customer Acquisition</h3>
							<ul>
								<li><strong>CAC Range:</strong> AED 60-90 (Bull to Bear)</li>
								<li><strong>Payback Period:</strong> 2.5-3.5 months target</li>
								<li><strong>Order Volume:</strong> 60-150 daily orders (Bear to Bull)</li>
							</ul>
						</div>
						
						<div class="assumption-card">
							<h3>Revenue Model</h3>
							<ul>
								<li><strong>AOV Range:</strong> AED 80-110 (Bear to Bull)</li>
								<li><strong>Contribution Margin:</strong> 32-42%</li>
								<li><strong>Order Frequency:</strong> 2.5 orders/customer/month</li>
							</ul>
						</div>
						
						<div class="assumption-card">
							<h3>Operational Efficiency</h3>
							<ul>
								<li><strong>Fixed Costs:</strong> AED 65K-110K monthly (lean to scaled)</li>
								<li><strong>Target LTV:CAC:</strong> > 3.5 ratio</li>
								<li><strong>Churn Rate:</strong> 7-12% monthly (excellent to conservative)</li>
							</ul>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="model-section">
			<div class="container">
				<FinancialModel client:load />
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="analysis-section">
			<div class="container">
				<h2>Financial Analysis & Insights</h2>
				
				<div class="insights-grid">
					<div class="insight-card">
						<h3>Unit Economics</h3>
						<p>
							Our base case model targets a 4.6 LTV:CAC ratio with AED 95 AOV and AED 75 CAC. 
							This provides strong unit economics with 2.8-month payback period, enabling rapid sustainable growth.
						</p>
						<div class="insight-metric">
							<span class="metric-number">4.6x</span>
							<span class="metric-label">LTV:CAC Ratio (Base Case)</span>
						</div>
					</div>

					<div class="insight-card">
						<h3>Scale Economics</h3>
						<p>
							Fixed costs of AED 180K/month become increasingly efficient as we scale. 
							Breakeven occurs around 50 orders/day, with strong margin expansion beyond 80 orders/day.
						</p>
						<div class="insight-metric">
							<span class="metric-number">50</span>
							<span class="metric-label">Daily orders breakeven target</span>
						</div>
					</div>

					<div class="insight-card">
						<h3>Cash Flow Profile</h3>
						<p>
							With AED 500K initial investment, base case projections show positive cumulative cash flow 
							by month 18-24, with strong acceleration thereafter as customer base compounds.
						</p>
						<div class="insight-metric">
							<span class="metric-number">18-24</span>
							<span class="metric-label">Months to cash flow positive</span>
						</div>
					</div>

					<div class="insight-card">
						<h3>Scenario Sensitivity</h3>
						<p>
							The model shows resilience across scenarios. Even in bear case (higher CAC, lower AOV), 
							profitability is achievable with disciplined execution and optimized customer acquisition.
						</p>
						<div class="insight-metric">
							<span class="metric-number">3</span>
							<span class="metric-label">Viable scenarios tested</span>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="caveats">
					<h3>Model Assumptions & Limitations</h3>
					<ul>
						<li>Linear growth assumptions may not reflect actual S-curve adoption patterns</li>
						<li>CAC assumes blended digital acquisition cost across social media and performance channels</li>
						<li>Churn rates based on industry averages; actual retention may vary with product-market fit</li>
						<li>Fixed costs may scale with growth requirements (fulfillment centers, staff)</li>
						<li>Model doesn't include potential revenue from advertising or marketplace commissions</li>
						<li>Seasonality and competitive dynamics not factored into projections</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>
	</main>
</MainLayout>

<style>
	.financials-page {
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #f8fafc 0%, #e2e8f0 100%);
		min-height: 100vh;
		transition: background 0.3s ease;
	}

	/* Dark mode for financials page */
	.dark-mode .financials-page {
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1a1a1a 0%, #2d2d2d 100%);
	}

	.container {
		max-width: 1200px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 0 2rem;
	}

	.breadcrumb {
		margin-bottom: 2rem;
		text-align: left;
	}

	.breadcrumb a {
		color: var(--color-secondary);
		text-decoration: none;
		font-weight: 500;
		transition: color 0.3s ease;
	}

	.breadcrumb a:hover {
		color: var(--color-primary);
	}

	.intro-section {
		padding: 4rem 0 2rem;
		text-align: center;
	}

	.intro-section h1 {
		font-size: 3rem;
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
		color: #1a202c;
	}

	.intro-text {
		font-size: 1.2rem;
		color: #4a5568;
		max-width: 600px;
		margin: 0 auto 3rem;
		line-height: 1.6;
	}

	.key-assumptions {
		text-align: left;
		margin-top: 3rem;
	}

	.key-assumptions h2 {
		text-align: center;
		margin-bottom: 2rem;
		color: #2d3748;
	}

	.assumptions-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
		gap: 2rem;
		margin-bottom: 3rem;
	}

	.assumption-card {
		background: var(--bg-card);
		padding: 2rem;
		border-radius: 12px;
		box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
	}

	.assumption-card h3 {
		margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
		color: #2ec4b6;
		font-size: 1.2rem;
	}

	.assumption-card ul {
		margin: 0;
		padding-left: 1.5rem;
		color: #4a5568;
		line-height: 1.6;
	}

	.assumption-card li {
		margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
	}

	.model-section {
		padding: 2rem 0;
		background: var(--bg-primary);
		border-radius: 24px 24px 0 0;
		margin-top: 2rem;
		box-shadow: var(--shadow-lg);
	}

	.analysis-section {
		padding: 3rem 0;
		background: var(--bg-primary);
	}

	.analysis-section h2 {
		text-align: center;
		margin-bottom: 3rem;
		color: #2d3748;
	}

	.insights-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
		gap: 2rem;
		margin-bottom: 3rem;
	}

	.insight-card {
		background: var(--bg-secondary);
		padding: 2rem;
		border-radius: 12px;
		border-left: 4px solid var(--color-secondary);
	}

	.insight-card h3 {
		margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
		color: #2d3748;
		font-size: 1.1rem;
	}

	.insight-card p {
		color: #4a5568;
		line-height: 1.6;
		margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
	}

	.insight-metric {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		text-align: center;
		padding: 1rem;
		background: rgba(46, 196, 182, 0.1);
		border-radius: 8px;
	}

	.metric-number {
		font-size: 2rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #2ec4b6;
		margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
	}

	.metric-label {
		font-size: 0.9rem;
		color: #4a5568;
	}

	.caveats {
		background: #fff5f5;
		padding: 2rem;
		border-radius: 12px;
		border-left: 4px solid #fed7d7;
	}

	.caveats h3 {
		margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
		color: #c53030;
	}

	.caveats ul {
		margin: 0;
		padding-left: 1.5rem;
		color: #4a5568;
		line-height: 1.6;
	}

	.caveats li {
		margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
	}

	@media (max-width: 768px) {
		.intro-section h1 {
			font-size: 2rem;
		}

		.assumptions-grid, .insights-grid {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}

		.container {
			padding: 0 1rem;
		}
	}
</style> 